Distribution. Known only from the Hamersley Range, a heavily dissected region of banded ironstone occupying the southern part of the Pilbara craton of Western Australia . Records span the Hamersley Range for over 300 km from east of Newman ( WAM R 125100 , WAM R 125456 ) west to Mount Rica ( WAM R 164579 ) and south to Rocklea Station ( WAM R
140734
) (Fig. 2 ).
